import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['rate'] = pd.to_numeric(data['rate'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['rate'], vert=False)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of rate across all states?')
    ax.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='r', label=f'Median: {data["rate"].median():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('region').mean()
    plt.bar(data.index, data['rate'])
    plt.title('How does the rate vary across different regions?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Region')
    plt.ylabel('Average Rate')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['state'], data['rate'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('State')
    ax.set_ylabel('Rate')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between rate and state?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['rate'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].mode()[0], color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Most common rate: {data['rate'].mode()[0]:.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the most common rate across all states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['state'] = data['state'].astype('category')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['state'] == state]['rate'] for state in data['state'].unique()], labels=data['state'].unique())
    ax.set_xlabel('State')
    ax.set_ylabel('Rate')
    plt.title('How does the rate vary within each state?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
